@node not14 "APEX DESIGNS AND BLITTERSOFT ANNOUNCE PARTNERSHIP"
               APEX DESIGNS AND BLITTERSOFT ANNOUNCE PARTNERSHIP
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

July 22, 2000 - Apex Designs (http://www.apex-designs.net/) today announced a
distribution agreement with Blittersoft (http://www.blittersoft.com/). This
agreement will allow Blittersoft to sell Payback
(http://www.apex-designs.net/payback.html), Apex Designs' GTA-style game for the
Amiga, through both their website and over the telephone. The game will also be
directly available through Apex Designs' website, which will accept credit and
debit cards.

Payback is a game that allows the player to find out what it would be like to be
a master criminal. It's entirely non-linear - to complete a level the player
simply has to obtain a certain number of points - how they get those points is
entirely up to them; they can do what the local kingpin tells them, uncover
secret missions or just go on a mad killing spree. There are lots of hidden
surprises to discover, so it will be necessary to play the game through several
times to find all the extras.

The game engine supports perspective correct texture mapping, environment
mapping (reflections), realistic shadows, alpha-channelling (lens flares,
explosions and shockwaves), 12 channel 3D sound and realistic physics. The game
will also be translated into several languages and is due for release in
November 2000.

About Apex Designs

Apex Designs have been writing high-quality games for the Amiga since 1994, and
have been releasing games on the Internet since 1996. For additional
information, please visit www.apex-designs.net or email
queries\@apex-designs.net.

About Blittersoft

Blittersoft have been serving the Amiga community for over ten years. With a
recent move into games publishing, we are extremely pleased to be able to offer
such a great title. For more information, visit www.blittersoft.com.
