From: Anthony <TheAntony\@bigfoot.com>

Charon v1.4 has been released. It can be downloaded from my homepage or from
Aminet.

Version 1.4 (31.7.2000)

   - Double click on an entry now starts downloading it immediately, regardless
     of "Maximum transfers" option (it acted just the same as "Start" button up
     to now).

   - Charon sometimes wouldn't resolve numeric IP addresses properly.

   - Added a gadget next to "Proxy" gadget which lists all proxies from
     "Proxies" page in settings window making it easy to set current proxy to
     one of those.

   - Added few more error messages that better explain what went wrong while
     connecting to a host.

   - Added workaround for some servers (or scripts) which send relative URLs in
     Location: header for redirection although HTTP standard specifically says
     that they have to be absolute.

   - While working on the above problem, fixed a much worse bug in handling
     Location: headers that could even cause a crash.

   - It is now possible to log into FTP servers which send their initial
     greeting using somewhat unusual (although perfectly legal) multiline
     response.

   - HTML links parser erroneously treated "./" as "../"

   - Fixed display of remaining time (it actually showed total length of the
     transfer). If I find another bug connected to this, I will have to
     seriously consider becoming a circus clown.

   - Most of numeric buttons in settings window have been changed to a special
     kind of numeric string gadgets. They allow input of numbers only in
     certain range and have bubble help to indicate which range is that.

   - New option: "Always find proxy" tells Charon to always try to set the proxy
     based on your current IP address, not only when you create an entry for the
     first time.

   - Del key is now shortcut for "Remove".

   - HTML parser now ignores mailto: links.

   - Active downloads window didn't update data percentage properly when the
     main window was hidden.

   - Now removes "blah" out of http://www.host.com/file.html#blah user entered
     URLs (which it should have been doing since ages ago, argh).

   - If "Directory structure" option is active (ie. it's not set to -1) and
     filename contains just name of directory, Charon will append index.html to
     it.

   - New menu item and ARexx option: "Export list over" which overwrites the
     file to which it writes the list instead of appending to it.

   - Removed some space between settings pages and save/use/cancel gadgets in
     settings window which sometimes caused MUI to render it in a rather
     strange way.

   - Moved "No proxy" gadget to Local1 page, next to "Proxy" gadget.

   - Charon now sets busy pointer whenever a list is loaded or saved.

   - Corrected spelling of ARexx command TRANSFEREDLENGTH to TRANSFERREDLENGTH.
     The old form is still accepted for compatibility rasons.

   - Added SETAUTHORISATION as synonym for SETAUTHORIZATION ARexx command.

   - Bubble help for main display which showed URL, proxy and percentage of an
     entry is now updated more regularly.

